<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1065] Add a ContentStreamDataSource to DIH to accept post data</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1065</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is a common requirement to push data to DIH. Currently it is not possible . If we have a ContentStreamDataSource it can easily solve this problem&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sample configuration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;dataSource type=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ContentStreamDataSource&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This datasource does not need any extra configuration. Make a normal POST request with the data as the body. The params remain same.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
